Debian systems
==============

If you're running a Debian based system or any distribution using apt and/or dpkg,
then you really should install the deb package, as marchobmenu uses dpkg triggers
to update the menu each time a package is installed/removed.
If you install from source, you'll need to run the menu daemon.


Installing from a package:
===========================

Debian package
--------------

After installing the package:

add the following line to your ~/.config/openbox/menu.xml file
<menu label="Applications" id="marchobmenu-applications" execute="/usr/lib/marchobmenu/mom.sh" />

You can also add the places menu.
Replace "~" by any directory you want as a starting point, and "thunar" by the file manager of your choice.
<menu label="Places" id="marchobmenu-places" execute="/usr/lib/marchobmenu/mom-places.py ~ thunar"/>
If you don't want files to show up in the menu:
<menu label="Places" id="marchobmenu-places" execute="/usr/lib/marchobmenu/mom-places.py ~ thunar false"/>

Other types of packages
-----------------------

start the daemon
/usr/lib/marchobmenu/mom-daemon start

If you want it to start automatically at login,
add the following line to your ~/.config/openbox/autostart.sh file
/usr/lib/marchobmenu/mom-daemon start &

Then refer to the Debian package instructions

For more infos, see http://wiki.github.com/ju1ius/marchobmenu/


Installing from source:
=======================

copy the "marchobmenu/usr/lib/marchobmenu" directory to your "/usr/lib directory"
$ sudo cp -R marchobmenu/usr/lib/marchobmenu /usr/lib

copy the "marchobmenu/etc/xdg/menus/mom-applications.menu" file to your "/etc/xdg/menus" directory
$ sudo cp marchobmenu/etc/xdg/menus/mom-applications.menu /etc/xdg/menus

start the daemon
/usr/lib/marchobmenu/mom-daemon start

If you want it to start automatically at login,
add the following line to your ~/.config/openbox/autostart.sh file
/usr/lib/marchobmenu/mom-daemon start &

add the following line to your ~/.config/openbox/menu.xml file
<menu label="Applications" id="marchobmenu-applications" execute="/usr/lib/marchobmenu/mom.sh" />

You can also add the places menu.
Replace "~" by any directory you want as a starting point, and "thunar" by the file manager of your choice.
<menu label="Places" id="marchobmenu-places" execute="/usr/lib/marchobmenu/mom-places.py ~ thunar"/>

For more infos, see http://wiki.github.com/ju1ius/marchobmenu/

